Future Improvements

Once version 1 works, version 2 could include:

Batch drag-and-drop support.
Automatic rotation of skewed scans before processing.
Duplicate detection to avoid saving the same employee twice.
OCR confidence scoring with a review queue for uncertain names.
Optional export to CSV containing employee name, source file, and output paths.
A small preview window showing the detected photo and signature before saving.
GPU acceleration (CUDA) for much faster processing on supported machines.
Training a custom YOLO model specifically on OES ID cards, making detection far more reliable than generic contour-based methods.
Development Roadmap

I'd build this in the following phases to keep the project maintainable:

Project setup: Create the folder structure, configuration system, logging, and GUI shell.
File ingestion: Support PDFs and common image formats, including batch processing.
Document analysis: Distinguish digital PDFs from scanned documents and normalize inputs.
Detection engine: Locate the employee photo, signature, and name using OpenCV/OCR (with a path to upgrade to YOLO later).
Extraction pipeline: Crop detected regions, remove backgrounds, enhance images, and save with the correct filenames.
Automation: Add multithreading, progress tracking, cancellation, and directory monitoring.
Packaging: Build a standalone Windows executable with all required offline models bundled.